<subSubSection id="C300A1C2795EFF92BEA67B44CA35F98A" pageId="7" pageNumber="46" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="8BA5F249795EFF92BEA67B44CC87FA4C" blockId="7.[151,1436,1361,1774]" pageId="7" pageNumber="46">
<emphasis id="B96E2E5B795EFF92BEA67B44C967FAB5" bold="true" box="[151,279,1361,1387]" pageId="7" pageNumber="46">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Predominantly yellow; postcranium black, upper third shining black without pruinescence; supraalar presutural setae absent; male tergite 8 acute distally. Female without pinnate scales on legs.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BA5F249795EFF92BEA67B8ACCC8FA3E" blockId="7.[151,1436,1361,1774]" pageId="7" pageNumber="46">
<materialsCitation id="3B72F814795EFF92BEA67B8ACCC4FA3E" collectionCode="ZMC" pageId="7" pageNumber="46" specimenCount="1" typeStatus="lectotype">
This is the type-species of 
<taxonomicName id="4C1A89CA795EFF92BFFD7B8ACA1AFA66" authorityName="Wiedemann" authorityYear="1817" box="[460,618,1439,1464]" class="Insecta" family="Empididae" genus="Macrostomus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="46" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
