<emphasis id="B96E2E5B795EFF92BEF47875C923F9A4" bold="true" box="[197,339,1632,1658]" pageId="7" pageNumber="46">Discussion.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="4C1A89CA795EFF92BF6D7874CAFFF9A4" baseAuthorityName="Fabricius" baseAuthorityYear="1805" box="[348,655,1633,1658]" class="Insecta" family="Empididae" genus="Macrostomus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="46" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ferrugineus">
<emphasis id="B96E2E5B795EFF92BF6D7874CAFFF9A4" box="[348,655,1633,1658]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="46">Macrostomus ferrugineus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
appears close to 
<taxonomicName id="4C1A89CA795EFF92BD507874CC64F9A4" authorityName="Rafael &amp; Cumming" authorityYear="2009" box="[865,1044,1633,1658]" class="Insecta" family="Empididae" genus="Macrostomus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="46" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fusciventris" status="n. sp.">
<emphasis id="B96E2E5B795EFF92BD507874CC64F9A4" box="[865,1044,1633,1658]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="46">M. fusciventris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<emphasis id="B96E2E5B795EFF92BA157875CC19F9A4" bold="true" box="[1060,1129,1632,1658]" pageId="7" pageNumber="46">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A25D9320795EFF92BA157875CC19F9A4" box="[1060,1129,1632,1658]" pageId="7" pageNumber="46" rank="species">n. sp.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
, 
<taxonomicName id="4C1A89CA795EFF92BA487874CD38F9A4" authorityName="Rafael &amp; Cumming" authorityYear="2009" box="[1145,1352,1632,1658]" class="Insecta" family="Empididae" genus="Macrostomus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="46" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="melanothorax" status="n. sp.">
<emphasis id="B96E2E5B795EFF92BA487874CCE1F9A4" box="[1145,1169,1633,1658]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="46">M</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="B96E2E5B795EFF92BA937874CD38F9A4" box="[1186,1352,1633,1658]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="46">melanothorax</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<emphasis id="B96E2E5B795EFF92BB697875CDECF9A4" bold="true" box="[1368,1436,1632,1658]" pageId="7" pageNumber="46">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A25D9320795EFF92BB697875CDECF9A4" box="[1368,1436,1632,1658]" pageId="7" pageNumber="46" rank="species">n. sp.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C1A89CA795EFF92BEF87892C905F97E" authorityName="Rafael &amp; Cumming" authorityYear="2009" box="[201,373,1671,1696]" class="Insecta" family="Empididae" genus="Macrostomus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="46" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fuscithorax" status="n. sp.">
<emphasis id="B96E2E5B795EFF92BEF87892C905F97E" box="[201,373,1671,1696]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="46">M. fuscithorax</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<emphasis id="B96E2E5B795EFF92BFB47892C9B9F97F" bold="true" box="[389,457,1671,1697]" pageId="7" pageNumber="46">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A25D9320795EFF92BFB47892C9B9F97F" box="[389,457,1671,1697]" pageId="7" pageNumber="46" rank="species">n. sp.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
on the basis of male tergite 8 being acute distally. 
<taxonomicName id="4C1A89CA795EFF92BA147892CD24F97E" baseAuthorityName="Fabricius" baseAuthorityYear="1805" box="[1061,1364,1671,1696]" class="Insecta" family="Empididae" genus="Macrostomus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="46" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ferrugineus">
<emphasis id="B96E2E5B795EFF92BA147892CD24F97E" box="[1061,1364,1671,1696]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="46">Macrostomus ferrugineus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is the only known species in this species-group without supra-alar presutural setae. The female is similar to that of 
<taxonomicName id="4C1A89CA795EFF92BEA678C1C9DDF930" authority="(Curran)" baseAuthorityName="Curran" box="[151,429,1748,1774]" class="Insecta" family="Empididae" genus="Macrostomus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="46" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fulvithorax">
<emphasis id="B96E2E5B795EFF92BEA678C1C94EF933" box="[151,318,1748,1773]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="46">M. fulvithorax</emphasis>
(Curran)
</taxonomicName>
, but has no pinnate scales on the hind tibia.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
